<paragraph blockId="58.[189,310,1915,1941]" box="[189,310,1915,1941]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1915,1941]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1915,1941]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[189,1400,1962,2025]" lastBlockId="59.[187,1399,265,406]" lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName authority="Block, 2022" authorityName="De Block" authorityYear="2022" box="[370,493,1963,1988]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Paracephaelis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gautieri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[370,493,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">P. gautieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[502,594,1963,1989]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having densely pubescent young shoots, petioles, and leaves (vs glabrous), longer stipules (
<quantity box="[496,606,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="7.0">7–12 mm</quantity>
vs 
<quantity box="[643,759,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4 mm</quantity>
long), longer bracteoles (ca 
<quantity box="[1084,1150,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
vs 
<quantity box="[1187,1325,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="0.95" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.7">0.7–1.2 mm</quantity>
long), sessile flowers (vs pedicels 
<quantity box="[514,611,265,291]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6 mm</quantity>
long), longer calyx tubes (
<quantity box="[926,1047,265,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
long in flowering stage, up to 
<quantity box="[189,258,303,330]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
long in fruiting stage vs ca 
<quantity box="[589,658,303,330]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long), and a different pubescence on calyx and ovary (densely covered with long, tawny hairs, appressed to spreading on the calyx and erect on the ovary in 
<taxonomicName authority="Block, 2022" authorityName="De Block" authorityYear="2022" box="[1246,1397,342,367]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Paracephaelis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ranirisonii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1246,1397,342,367]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">P. ranirisonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[187,278,380,406]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
vs densely covered with shorter, whitish, appressed hairs in 
<taxonomicName authority="Block, 2022" authorityName="De Block" authorityYear="2022" box="[990,1112,380,405]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Paracephaelis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gautieri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[990,1112,380,405]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">P. gautieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1119,1214,380,406]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
